SECTION A: Classes and Objects (Basic)
Questions 1-10: Simple Level

Basic Class Creation
Create a class Car with attributes: brand, model, year. Create 3 objects and display their information.


Calculator Class
Create a Calculator class with methods for add, subtract, multiply, and divide. Test all methods.


Book Class
Create a Book class with attributes: title, author, price, pages. Add a method to display book info and another to check if it's expensive (price > $50).


Rectangle Class
Create a Rectangle class with length and width. Add methods to calculate area and perimeter.


Employee Class
Create an Employee class with name, id, and salary. Add a method to give a 10% raise.


Circle Class
Create a Circle class with radius. Add methods to calculate area and circumference (Ï€ = 3.14159).


Temperature Converter
Create a class Temperature that converts Celsius to Fahrenheit and vice versa.


Counter Class
Create a Counter class that can increment, decrement, and reset a counter value.


Time Class
Create a Time class with hours, minutes, seconds. Add a method to convert to total seconds.


Person Class
Create a Person class with name, age, and city. Add a method to check if person is adult (age >= 18).



Questions 11-20: Medium Level

Library Book Manager
Create a Library class that maintains a list of books. Add methods to add_book, remove_book, and display_all_books.


Shopping Cart
Create a ShoppingCart class that can add items, remove items, calculate total price, and apply discount.


Bank Account with Transaction History
Extend the BankAccount class to maintain transaction history (deposits and withdrawals).


Student Grade Manager
Create a Student class that stores multiple subject grades and calculates GPA, highest grade, and lowest grade.


Hotel Room Booking
Create a HotelRoom class with room_number, type, price, and booking status. Add methods to book and checkout.


Inventory System
Create an Item class for inventory with name, quantity, price. Add methods to update stock and calculate total value.


ATM Machine
Create an ATM class that handles multiple operations: check balance, withdraw, deposit, mini statement.


Contact Book
Create a Contact class with name, phone, email. Create a ContactBook class to manage multiple contacts.


Quiz System
Create a Question class and Quiz class that stores questions, takes answers, and calculates score.


Parking Lot
Create a ParkingLot class that manages parking spots, tracks available spaces, and calculates parking fees.




SECTION B: Inheritance and Polymorphism
Questions 21-30: Medium to Hard

Vehicle Hierarchy
Create a base class Vehicle and inherit Car, Bike, and Truck. Each should have specific attributes and methods.


Shape Calculator
Create a base class Shape with method area(). Create child classes Square, Circle, Triangle with their own area calculations.


Employee Management
Create base class Employee and inherit Manager, Developer, Intern with different salary calculations and benefits.


Animal Sound System
Create Animal base class and inherit Dog, Cat, Cow, Bird. Implement polymorphism for make_sound() method.


Payment System
Create Payment base class and inherit CreditCard, DebitCard, UPI, Cash with different processing methods.


Media Player
Create Media base class and inherit Audio, Video, Image with different play/display methods.


Bank Account Types
Create Account base class and inherit SavingsAccount, CurrentAccount, FixedDeposit with different interest calculations.


E-commerce Product System
Create Product base class and inherit Electronics, Clothing, Food with different discount and warranty policies.


School Management
Create Person base class and inherit Student, Teacher, Staff with different attributes and methods.


Sports Team
Create Player base class and inherit Batsman, Bowler, AllRounder with different statistics tracking.


SECTION C: File Handling (Basic)
Questions 31-40: Simple to Medium

Text File Creator
Write a program to create a text file and write 5 lines of your choice. Then read and display the content.


Line Counter
Write a program to count the number of lines in a text file.


Word Counter
Write a program to count total words in a text file.


Character Counter
Count total characters, vowels, and consonants in a text file.


File Copy
Write a program to copy content from one file to another.


File Append
Write a program that asks user for input and appends it to an existing file.


Search in File
Write a program to search for a specific word in a file and display line numbers where it appears.


Replace Text
Write a program to replace all occurrences of a word in a file with another word.


File Merge
Write a program to merge contents of two files into a third file.


Reverse File Content
Read a file and write its content in reverse order to a new file.




SECTION D: Exception Handling
Questions 41-50: Simple to Medium

Safe Division
Write a function that performs division and handles ZeroDivisionError and TypeError.


List Access
Create a program that accesses list elements and handles IndexError gracefully.


File Reader with Exception
Write a program to read a file and handle FileNotFoundError and PermissionError.


Integer Input Validator
Write a program that keeps asking for an integer until valid input is provided.


Dictionary Key Access
Create a dictionary and access keys with proper KeyError handling.


Multiple Exception Handler
Write a program that can raise and handle at least 4 different types of exceptions.


Age Validator
Create a function that validates age (must be between 0-120) with custom exception.


File Write with Exception
Write a program that handles exceptions while writing to a file (disk full, permission denied).


Calculator with Exceptions
Create a calculator that handles all possible exceptions (division by zero, invalid input, etc.).


Custom Exception for Grade
Create a custom exception InvalidGradeError for grade validation (0-100).




SECTION E: Combined OOP + File Handling
Questions 51-60: Medium to Hard

Student Records System
Create a Student class and save/load student data from a file. Include add, delete, search, and update operations.


Employee Payroll System
Create Employee class with file storage. Calculate salary, generate payslips, and save to files.


Library Management System
Create Book and Member classes. Store data in files. Implement issue, return, and fine calculation.


Expense Tracker
Create an Expense class that logs all expenses to a file. Generate monthly reports and category-wise analysis.


Todo List Application
Create Task class with priority and deadline. Save tasks to file. Mark complete, delete, and filter tasks.


Contact Management System
Create Contact class with CRUD operations. Store in file. Add search by name, phone, or email.


Inventory Management
Create Product class. Store inventory in file. Track stock levels, low stock alerts, and reorder.


Banking System
Create Account class with transaction logging to file. Generate account statements and transaction history.


Hospital Management
Create Patient and Appointment classes. Store records in files. Book appointments, view history.


Grade Book System
Create classes for Student, Course, and Grade. Store in files. Calculate GPA, generate transcripts.




SECTION F: Advanced Scenarios and Projects
Questions 61-75: Hard Level Projects

Restaurant Order Management
Create Menu, Order, Customer classes. Save orders to file. Calculate bills, apply discounts, generate daily sales report.


Hotel Reservation System
Create Room, Booking, Guest classes. Persist data in files. Handle bookings, cancellations, room availability, billing.


Online Quiz Application
Create Question, Quiz, User classes. Store questions in file. Track user scores, generate leaderboard, save results.


E-commerce Shopping System
Create Product, Customer, Order, Cart classes. File storage for all data. Handle orders, payments, order history.


Fitness Tracker
Create User, Workout, Diet classes. Log daily activities to files. Generate weekly reports, calorie tracking.


Movie Ticket Booking
Create Movie, Theatre, Booking classes. Store show times, bookings in files. Handle seat selection, cancellation.


School Attendance System
Create Student, Class, Attendance classes. Mark attendance in files. Generate attendance reports, defaulter lists.


Vehicle Rental System
Create Vehicle, Customer, Rental classes. Store rental records. Calculate rental charges, late fees, availability.


Blood Bank Management
Create Donor, Blood, Request classes. Maintain inventory in files. Track donations, requests, expiry dates.


Event Management System
Create Event, Participant, Venue classes. Store event details in files. Handle registrations, send confirmations.


Library Fine Calculator
Extend library system with fine calculation based on days overdue. Generate fine reports, payment tracking.


Electricity Billing System
Create Customer, Meter, Bill classes. Calculate bills based on units consumed. Save billing history to files.


Exam Management System
Create Student, Exam, Result classes. Store exam schedules, marks in files. Generate report cards, merit lists.


Pharmacy Management
Create Medicine, Sale, Inventory classes. Track medicine stock, expiry dates, sales. Generate reports.


Social Media Post Manager
Create User, Post, Comment classes. Store posts in files. Implement like, comment, share features. Generate user activity reports.




SECTION G: Error Handling Scenarios
Questions 76-85: Exception-Focused

File Processing Pipeline
Create a program that reads data from one file, processes it, writes to another. Handle all possible file-related exceptions.


Network Data Saver (Simulated)
Simulate downloading data and saving to file. Handle connection errors, file errors, data format errors.


CSV Data Processor
Read CSV file with student data. Handle missing fields, invalid data types, calculate statistics with exception handling.


Configuration File Reader
Read configuration from file. Handle missing file, invalid format, missing keys with appropriate defaults.


Log File Analyzer
Read log files and extract errors. Handle large files, corrupted data, missing timestamps.


Backup System
Create a backup system that copies files. Handle permission errors, disk space issues, missing source files.


Data Validator
Read data file and validate each entry. Create error log for invalid entries. Handle all exceptions gracefully.


Multi-file Report Generator
Read data from multiple files and generate a report. Handle missing files, inconsistent formats.


Safe File Deletion
Create a program to delete files safely with confirmation. Handle FileNotFoundError, PermissionError.


JSON Data Handler
Read and write JSON files with student records. Handle JSON decode errors, file errors.




SECTION H: Real-World Applications
Questions 86-100: Project-Based

Personal Budget Manager
Track income and expenses by category. Save to files. Generate monthly budgets, savings reports, expense trends.


Appointment Scheduler
Create a scheduling system for appointments. Handle time conflicts, reminders, cancellations. Save all data to files.


Recipe Manager
Store recipes with ingredients and steps. Search by ingredients, category. Save/load from files. Calculate nutritional info.


Gym Membership System
Manage members, membership plans, attendance. Calculate fees, track renewals. Store all data in files.


Course Registration System
Create system for students to register for courses. Handle prerequisites, capacity limits, conflicts. Save to files.


Parking Management System
Track vehicle entry/exit, calculate parking fees based on time. Handle different vehicle types. Generate daily revenue reports.


Hospital Patient Management
Register patients, assign doctors, track appointments, maintain medical history. Store everything in files with proper exception handling.


Library Fine Management
Track borrowed books, calculate fines for overdue books. Generate fine reports, payment tracking. Send reminders.


Employee Leave Management
Track employee leaves (sick, casual, earned). Calculate leave balance, approve/reject leaves. Store records in files.


Bus Reservation System
Manage bus routes, bookings, seat availability. Calculate fares, handle cancellations. Store booking data in files.


Online Food Ordering
Create menu, take orders, calculate bills with taxes and delivery charges. Store order history. Generate restaurant reports.


Warehouse Management
Track inventory, incoming/outgoing stock, reorder levels. Generate stock reports, alerts for low stock.


Voting System
Create a secure voting system with voter registration, vote casting, result calculation. Store data securely in files.


Music Library Manager
Store songs with metadata (artist, album, genre, duration). Create playlists, search songs, generate statistics.


Travel Booking System
- Book flights/hotels/packages. Handle passenger details, pricing, discounts, cancellations. Generate booking confirmations and invoices.


